    <p class="tools">
              <a href="..\/images\/84009_2028981.jpg" class="enlargement-link enlargement-link-144799"><strong>View</strong> enlargement</a><br />
                          <a href="http://www.artic.edu/aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/144799/email"><strong>Email</strong> to a friend</a><br />
                    <a href="http://www.artic.edu/aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/144799/print" target="_blank"><strong>Print</strong> this page</a>          </p>
    <!--/tools-->
  
    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Irving Penn<br />
American, 1917–2009<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>Cecil Beaton, London</em>, 1950, printed March/April 1977</h3>

    <p>
    Platinum-palladium print, edition 8/15<br />    38.2 x 37.1 cm (image); 52 x 51 cm (paper)<br />    Inscribed verso: “119 / .. [in a circle]”; inscribed verso: “CECIL BEATON [in a box] / PHOTOGRAPHED IN LONDON, 1950.”; inscribed verso: “BF 360 Paper on Aluminum / Multiple Coating and Printing / 1 [in a circle] Platinum / 2 [in a circle] Platinum-palladium / Print made March–April 1977.”; stamped verso: “DEACIDIFIED”; inscribed verso: “8/15”; stamped verso: “PHOTOGRAPH BY IRVING PENN / Copyright © 1958 by / LES EDITIONS CONDE NAST S.A. / Not to be reproduced without / written permission of the / copyright owner.”; stamped and inscribed verso: “In addition to 15 numbered prints of this image / in platinum metals, unnumbered, but signed silver / prints not exceeding a total of 15 may exist.”; signed and stamped verso: “Irving Penn / Hand-coated by the photographer [in a circle].”<br />    Gift of Irving Penn, 1996.206</p>
        Copyright Les Editions Condé Nast S.A.
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

  </div>
  <!--/artwork-details-->

    
      <div id="artwork-body">
                <div id="abbrev">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/more" class="more">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
      <!--content hidden-->
    </div>
    <div id="extended">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/less" class="less">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
            <h2>Exhibition History</h2>
      <p>Chicago, Art Institute of Chicago, “Irving Penn, A Career in Photography,” November 22, 1997–February 1, 1998; traveled to St. Petersburg, Russia, State Hermitage Museum, March 1–May 16, 1998; Hamburg, Germany, Deichtorhallen, June 18–September 6, 1998; Munich, Germany, Müchner Stadtmuseum, October 6, 1998–February 21, 1999; San Francisco, California, Friends of Photography/Ansel Adams Center for Photography, November 11, 1999–January 23, 2000; Museum of Fine Arts, Houston, March 25–June 4, 2000; Paris, France, Maison Européenne de la Photographie, September 13–November 5, 2000. (Colin Westerbeck)</p>
                  <h2>Publication History</h2>
      <p>Penn, Irving. 1960. “Moments Preserved.” Simon and Schuster. p. 85. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Varnedoe, Kirk. 1976. "Modern Portraits: the Self and Others." Exh. cat. Department of Art History and Archaeology, Columbia University/Wildenstein Gallery. p. 124, fig. 91. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Marlborough Fine Art, London. 1981. “Irving Penn: Photographs in Platinum Metals, Images 1947–1975.” Marlborough Fine Art London. p. 8, cat. 7. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Szarkowski, John. 1984. "Irving Penn." Exh. cat. Museum of Modern Art/New York Graphic Society Books. pl. 21. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Museum Ludwig. 1984. “Sammlung Gruber: Photographie des 20. Jarhunderts.” Exh. cat. Museum Ludwig. p. 341. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Foresta, Merry A. and William F. Stapp. 1990. “Irving Penn: Master Images.” Exh. cat. National Museum of American Art and National Portrait Gallery/Smithsonian Institution Press. p. 39, cat. 26. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Penn, Irving. 1991. “Passage: A Work Record.” Knopf. p. 95. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Hürlimann, Annemarie. 1994. “Irving Penn: Collection privée/Irving Penn: Privatsammlung.” Exh. cat. Musée d’art et d’histoire/Editions Bentali. p. 30, cat. 30. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Westerbeck, Colin. 1997. “Irving Penn: A Career in Photography.” Exh. cat. Art Institute of Chicago/Bulfinch Press. p. 30, cat. 61, pl. 6.<br />
<br />
Greenough, Sarah. 2005. “Irving Penn: Platinum Prints.” Exh. cat. National Gallery of Art/Yale University Press. pl. 25. (other print of this image)</p>
                  <h2>Ownership History</h2>
      <p>Given by the artist to the Art Institute, 1996.</p>
